OL,4,CClimate change: Consumer 'confusion'
OL,5,Cthreatens net zero homes plan
OL,6, Government plans to decarbonise homes
OL,7, are too complicated and confusing,
OL,8, according to a coalition of consumer
OL,9, and industry groups.
OL,11,FThey've written to the prime minister
OL,12,Fto say that current schemes to adapt
OL,13,Fhomes go wrong far too often.
OL,15,FThe open letter, from Citizens Advice
OL,16,Fand others, calls for more financial
OL,17,Fsupport for making changes.
OL,19,FOtherwise, they argue, efforts to curb
OL,20,Femissions from millions of homes in the
OL,21,FUK will be at risk.
